cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.CY 

The paper deals with the utilization of user-provided tags for resource classification, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the characteristics and nature of social tagging systems, which involves social interactions and user-generated content, making cs.SI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of automated classifiers, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.DL and cs.CY.
